<br>
Get at *MAX* bolt range for pull and hit it with a cinder bolt.  Immediately start casting blaze and face the opposite way from your mob (so you can start running as soon as the nuke lands).  Hopefully you can land the blaze before the mob gets to you (you most likely will).  This should keep the mob on you most of the fight.  <br>
<br>
A trick I use to see if the pet has gotten aggro or not is to not kite in a straight line, rather a circle.  Make this a tight circle, but not tight enough that the mob keeps up with you.  If the pet gets aggro, you will see that pretty quick in your circle.  <br>
<br>
A little trick you can use to extend it before you have to nuke again or if you are LoM is to sit down.  If the mob just turned onto the pet and pets taunt is off, the mob will start comming after you again.  Stand up before the mob gets within melee range...back up a bit and sit down again.  You can keep alot of attacks off your pet by doing this.<br>
<br>
Ultimately this is best done with sow/jboots/tboots/run3, but with specs, you can probably do it without them.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps.  =) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urazha.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Razha</A> at: 6/4/02 4:33:56 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uiwanthewicca.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IwanTheWicca</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#333333>(6/5/02 6:11:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=380.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Do I Malise?</span><hr size=1> Thanks for all that info <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
