<br>
Things to know ahead of time:<br>
     Specs move SLOW,<br>
     Specs cast FEAR,<br>
     Pet's are no longer KoS to anything<br>
     Nukes are pretty efficient at your lvl (34+)<br>
<br>
Pull method is the tough part.  I'm assuming since you're already killing specs that you have this taken care.<br>
<br>
Preferred method:  Turn the pets taunt OFF and pull with Malosini (or your equivilant).  Best to pull to the SRo area or keep it in the area with the fisherman.  Safest spot for your fellow players.  You can stay out of range quite easily.  Nuke it 2 or 3 times BEFORE you send in your pet, unless a fear lands.  IF the spec's attention gets focused on your pet, you have two choices.  Either nuke it and get it back on you, OR turn your pets taunt ON and cast a rain spell.  These are very sweet damage for the mana they use and not often resisted.  As soon as you cast the rain spell, start casting a nuke as well.  This will give you a double wammy as the 3rd wave hits and probably regain the specs attention.<br>
<br>
Other method:  Turn pets taunt ON, pull to land with a buffed pet and after you land malosini, cast a rain and then a DD immediately after.  This will probably get it on you, but the pet will quickly get it back and after 10 seconds or so, cast another rain and DD immediately after.  When I say immediately, I mean as soon as the icons appear and it's possible to cast, NOT after all 3 waves go by.<br>
<br>
Also, congrats.  34 is, IMO, the first or second most powerful lvl you'll be in the game for your lvl.  You actually are capable of soloing mobs that are even red if you're careful and selective and develop a strategy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zhkronik>zH KroNiK</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 12:19:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=380.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: How the hell do I kite specs??</span><hr size=1> This is what I find to be the best way to kill specters (did this w/ my mage at 39ish and it was easy) First off, not Feerrott, Oasis of Marr. What you need to do this is. SoW and KEI<br>
#1 Don't Make Pet<br>
#2 Make sure you have SoW and KEI<br>
#3 only spells your using are Cinder Bolt and Blaze (use bracelet)<br>
#4 bind yourself on the bank thats closest to spec island<br>
#5 go run to spec island on the penninsula<br>
#6 cast cinder bolt on the specter<br>
#7 go run to end of penninsula and gate back (if you have levi run to land)<br>
#8 you'll get 4-5 spectres<br>
#9 all you do is run, stop and cast cinder bolt<br>
